comment: /**  * Returns the name of this execution vertex in the format "myTask (2/7)".  *  * @return name of this execution vertex  */
code: /**  * Returns the name of this execution vertex in the format "myTask (2/7)".  *  * @return name of this execution vertex  */ String getTaskNameWithSubtaskIndex().

comment: /**  * Returns the subtask index of this execution vertex.  *  * @return subtask index of this execution vertex.  */
code: /**  * Returns the subtask index of this execution vertex.  *  * @return subtask index of this execution vertex.  */ int getParallelSubtaskIndex().

comment: /**  * Returns the current execution for this execution vertex.  *  * @return current execution  */
code: /**  * Returns the current execution for this execution vertex.  *  * @return current execution  */ AccessExecution getCurrentExecutionAttempt().

comment: /**  * Returns the current {@link ExecutionState} for this execution vertex.  *  * @return execution state for this execution vertex  */
code: /**  * Returns the current {@link ExecutionState} for this execution vertex.  *  * @return execution state for this execution vertex  */ ExecutionState getExecutionState().

comment: /**  * Returns the timestamp for the given {@link ExecutionState}.  *  * @param state state for which the timestamp should be returned  * @return timestamp for the given state  */
code: /**  * Returns the timestamp for the given {@link ExecutionState}.  *  * @param state state for which the timestamp should be returned  * @return timestamp for the given state  */ long getStateTimestamp(ExecutionState state).

comment: /**  * Returns the exception that caused the job to fail. This is the first root exception  * that was not recoverable and triggered job failure.  *  * @return failure exception as a string, or {@code "(null)"}  */
code: /**  * Returns the exception that caused the job to fail. This is the first root exception  * that was not recoverable and triggered job failure.  *  * @return failure exception as a string, or {@code "(null)"}  */ String getFailureCauseAsString().

comment: /**  * Returns the {@link TaskManagerLocation} for this execution vertex.  *  * @return taskmanager location for this execution vertex.  */
code: /**  * Returns the {@link TaskManagerLocation} for this execution vertex.  *  * @return taskmanager location for this execution vertex.  */ TaskManagerLocation getCurrentAssignedResourceLocation().

comment: /**  * Returns the execution for the given attempt number.  *  * @param attemptNumber attempt number of execution to be returned  * @return execution for the given attempt number  */
code: /**  * Returns the execution for the given attempt number.  *  * @param attemptNumber attempt number of execution to be returned  * @return execution for the given attempt number  */ AccessExecution getPriorExecutionAttempt(int attemptNumber).
